properties.headline: Gale Watch issued February 7 at 2:49AM PST until February 8 at 9:00PM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, northwest winds 20 to 30
kt with gusts up to 35 kt expected. For the Gale Watch,
northwest winds 25 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and seas 7
to 11 feet at 13 seconds possible.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Point Arena to Point Reyes
California out to 10 nm.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from noon today to 9 AM
PST Saturday. For the Gale Watch, from Saturday morning
through Saturday evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 9 AM PST SATURDAY... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING
